-- Honda's U.S. sales fall adjusted 0.2 percent in October
-- 
-- Thu Nov 1, 2007 1:42pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/01/us-honda-sales-us-idUSWNAS983220071101

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - Honda Motor Co ( 7267.T ) on Thursday said its U.S. sales fell 0.2 percent in October. 

 The Japanese automaker said it sold 114,799 Honda and Acura vehicles in the United States last month, including results for its luxury Acura brand. That compared with 110,624 vehicles a year earlier. The results were adjusted for the extra selling day last month.